===People groups===
* [[Afrikaner Calvinism|Boer Calvinists]]: [[Boere-Afrikaner]]s that hold to Reformed Theology.
* [[Huguenot]]s: followers of Calvinism in France, the 16th and 17th century.
* [[Pilgrims (Plymouth Colony)|Pilgrim]]s: Puritan separatists who left Europe for America in search of religious toleration.
* [[Presbyterians]]: originate in [[Scotland]]
* [[Puritan]]s: English
* [[Continental Reformed churches]]: Calvinist churches originating in continental Europe
* [[Waldensians]]: Italian, precede Calvinism but some today identify with Reformed theology

